			<title>D : The Safest Ways to Use Your GCB MasterCard</title>
			<link>http://www.gcb.com.gh/products-services/electronic-banking/d-the-safest-ways-to-use-your-gcb-mastercard</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.gcb.com.gh/products-services/electronic-banking/d-the-safest-ways-to-use-your-gcb-mastercard</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p>The GCB MasterCard Debit cards are important payment instruments and for the protection of cardholders, they (cards) need to be properly taken care of.</p>
<p>Here are few safety tips and best ways to use your GCB MasterCard:</p>
<ul>
<li>Keep your card in a secure place, and treat it as if it was cash. Always store it in the protective sleeve.</li>
<li>Remember to take back your card after completing your transaction at any Automated Teller Machine (ATM) or Point of Sale (POS) device.</li>
<li>Do not bend your card or place it close to other magnetic materials, or expose it to direct sunlight.</li>
<li>Never give your card to anyone.</li>
<li>Do not accept assistance from strangers when using your card.</li>
<li>Keep your PIN private. Destroy the PIN advice after memorizing it.</li>
<li>You can change your PIN at any time on GCB ATMs.</li>
<li>As extra security and precautionary measure, regularly change your PIN at any GCB ATM.</li>
<li>Never write your PIN on your card.</li>
<li>Make sure no one sees your PIN when you use it on an ATM or POS device.</li>
<li>Always observe your surroundings before conducting an ATM transaction.</li>
<li>If you use an outdoor ATM, use one that is well lit and visible.</li>
<li>Always be aware, alert and prepared to act when visiting an ATM.</li>
<li>Minimize time spent at the ATM.</li>
<li>Do not just walk straight up to an ATM. Always look around for suspicious cars or persons.</li>
<li>Do not count money while at the ATM. Do not flash cash. Do not dress expensively.</li>
<li>Do not leave receipts lying around. (Take them with you.) Do not put them in the trash container near the machine.</li>
<li>Trust your instincts. If you feel something is wrong, go to another machine.</li>
<li>If anything suspicious happens, cancel your transaction and leave the area.</li>
<li>Check your receipts against your monthly statements to guard against ATM fraud.</li>
</ul>
<p>Report a lost or stolen card immediately.</p>
<p>Immediately your card is lost or stolen, please contact:</p>
<p>GCB Electronic Banking Call Centre<br />Tel: +233 . 21 . 246025 or +233 . 21. 254101; Fax: +233 . 21 . 246032<br />Email: mastercard@gcb.com.gh</p></div>]]></description>
			<author>prelations@gcb.com.gh (GCB)</author>
