			<title>A : What is GCB MasterCard?</title>
			<link>http://www.gcb.com.gh/products-services/electronic-banking/a-what-is-gcb-mastercard</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">http://www.gcb.com.gh/products-services/electronic-banking/a-what-is-gcb-mastercard</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<div class="feed-description"><p>GCB broke new grounds with the introduction of MasterCard product and services in Ghana late last year. The GCB MasterCard is a 'Must have' card that offers financial flexibility, convenience and security.</p>
<p><strong>What is MasterCard Worldwide?</strong></p>
<p>MasterCard is a global payment solution company that manages a family of well known and widely accepted payment card brands and ATMs through financial institutions.</p>
<p>MasterCard payment products and solutions offer comprehensive card programs that feature state-of-the-art security and convenience. MasterCard's wide variety of customized card types include credit, debit, prepaid, commercial, chip and contactless. With innovative loyalty and reward solutions and comprehensive cardholder benefits and services, MasterCard card products provide financial institutions, merchants, and businesses with inventive ways to decrease costs and increase customer satisfaction</p>
<p><strong>What is GCB MasterCard?</strong></p>
<p>The GCB MasterCard Debit card is an international electronic card that allows cardholders to transact business through numerous MasterCard branded Automated Teller Machines (ATMs) and Point of Sale (POS) terminals worldwide.</p>
<p><strong>The GCB MasterCard Debit cards are fully functional.</strong></p>
<p>In Ghana, the GCB MasterCard Debit cards can be used on all GCB ATMs in addition to ATMs of other banks like Stanbic Bank.</p>
<p>Additionally, the GCB MasterCard Debit cards also work on the MasterCard branded Point of Sale (POS) or Points of Interaction devices in about 280 countries as well as over 12 million locations worldwide.</p>
<p>Immediately your card is lost or stolen, please contact:</p>
<p>GCB Electronic Banking Call Centre<br />Tel: +233 . 21 . 246025 or +233 . 21. 254101; Fax: +233 . 21 . 246032<br />Email: mastercard@gcb.com.gh</p></div>]]></description>
